The Service Party (TSP) leader Mwangi Kiunjuri (pictured) has asked Meru residents to elect a presidential candidate who will champion their well-being.   Kiunjuri, who was in the company of TSP Secretary-General Mwenda Makathimo and Meru assembly deputy speaker Elias Murega asked voters to elect a president, who will revive agriculture activities.    "As Mt Kenya and Meru people, we must put them to task on how they will economically uplift us," said Kiunjuri.   He noted that Deputy President William Ruto, ODM Leader Raila Odinga, Wiper Party boss Kalonzo Musyoka and other candidates must convince voters that they will work to promote development in the agricultural sector.  Raila to Musalia: Don’t oppose my Sh6,000-for-the-poor plan  Kiraitu and Munya asked to decamp as DP Ruto ends tour  Give us a break! Mt Kenya governors tell Ruto  Harold, Sue in all-out appeal to voters in rival churches Kiunjuri was speaking during the opening of a new office in Gatimbi.  He also asked the Mount Kenya people to remain united and avoid any form of violence.     Exploring the preparedness and the key timeliness of the IEBC to conduct the 2022 General Elections  John Mbadi: From 2014 to around this time we have mismanaged our economy  Should BBI be pigeon-holed into the current economic circumstances? | The Way It Is | Part 2 By Timothy Kariuki | 3 hours ago By Patrick Beja | 5 hours ago By Josphat Thiong’o | 5 hours ago By Phares Mutembei | 11 hours ago